sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant C as CLI
    participant A as API
    participant D as DB

    U->>C: Enter current password and new password
    C->>A: GET /auth/me/bootstrap (Bearer JWT)
    A->>D: Load user bootstrap material
    D-->>A: enc_urk, enc_urk_nonce, kek_salt
    A-->>C: bootstrap payload

    C->>C: Derive old KEK from current password
    C->>C: Decrypt URK with old KEK
    C->>C: Derive new KEK from new password
    C->>C: Re-encrypt same URK with new KEK

    C->>A: POST /auth/change-password\n(current_password, new_password,\nnew enc_urk, new nonce, new salt)
    A->>D: Verify current password hash
    A->>D: Update password_hash
    A->>D: Update enc_urk, enc_urk_nonce, kek_salt
    D-->>A: commit success
    A-->>C: Password changed successfully

    Note over C,D: File ciphertexts stay unchanged.\nOnly the wrapping path to recover URK is rotated.
